        <p>After you insert a page number into a frame, you can specify the format of the number (e.g., decimal, lowercase Roman, uppercase alpha). You can also specify whether the numbering should begin at a certain number. Both of these tasks can be accomplished when you associate the page layout with a TOC entry. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <xref href="../../../../Flare/Page-Layouts/Process/Specifying-Chapter-Breaks1.htm">Specifying Chapter Breaks and Page Layouts</xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/See-Online-Help.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="Flare-Guides.Flare-Printed-Output-Guide" /></p>
